<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER PROPOSITION 128 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The time has come to control all harmful toxins, stop pollution and prevent any 
further destruction of the environment. If severe and rigid legal methods are 
required through the passage of Prop. 128, then so be it. 
</P>
<P>
Big business profits will go down, although the salaries of company presidents 
and their executives will assuredly not. Instead of restructuring to be 
environmentally safe and, in the long run saving jobs and lives, big 
corporations are pumping money into advertising against Big Green. 
</P>
<P>
Gov. Deukmejian, (gubernatorial candidate) Sen. Pete Wilson and large 
corporations have had their chance to protect the environment and the health of 
all of us. They have done next to nothing. 
</P>
<P>
Are lives more important, or business? 
</P>
<P>
DEAN H. du VERNET 
</P>
<P>
Northridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
