<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TEEN ARRESTED IN KILLING OF WOMAN, 68, IN 
DRIVE-BY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies on Tuesday arrested a Los Angeles teen-ager suspected of 
fatally shooting a 68-year-old woman during a drive-by as she sat on the front 
porch of her Walnut Park home with her granddaughter in her lap. 
</P>
<P>
Andre Bell, 19, was taken into custody at his home by deputies investigating 
the Aug. 16 shooting of Anna Owens, who was hit in the chest by a stray bullet 
while she held her 9-month-old granddaughter, said Sheriff's Department 
spokesman Rich Erickson. 
</P>
<P>
Owens' granddaughter was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
An assault rifle and a handgun were also recovered during the arrest, but 
Erickson said investigators are unsure if either of the guns was used to kill 
Owens. 
</P>
<P>
Bell was booked on suspicion of murder and was being held without bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
