<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
SHOOTING OF 3 CALLED ATYPICAL OF GANGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT LAWRENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A drive-by shooting in Ventura that left three men injured Sunday was not a 
typical gang attack, Police Sgt. Bob Anderson said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
In a gang shooting, one or two shots are usually fired from a speeding vehicle 
at unsuspecting victims, he said. 
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's incident, eight to 10 shots were fired, and evidence suggests that 
the gunshots came from two directions, Anderson said. The victims did not 
return fire, he said. 
</P>
<P>
John Michael Hart, 20, of Fillmore and Michael Wade, 26, and Noe Perez, 30, of 
Ventura were in fair but stable condition Tuesday with broken bones, a Ventura 
Medical Center spokesman said. The three victims were standing in the 2400 
block of Channel Drive about 12:30 a.m. Sunday when they were struck in the 
legs by shotgun pellets, Anderson said. SCOTT LAWRENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
