<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: OTAY MESA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 5-year-old girl suffered severe injuries Tuesday when she was hit by a 
speeding car driven by an unlicensed driver, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Vanessa Espinoza, whose address was not available, was walking in the 1500 
block of Kenalan Drive in Otay Mesa about 4:20 p.m. when she was hit by a car 
driven by a 16-year-old without a driver's license, San Diego police said. 
</P>
<P>
Vanessa suffered head injuries and a broken leg, police said. She was taken to 
Children's Hospital, where she was being operated on Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
The driver's identity was not available. The car was traveling about 45 m.p.h. 
in a residential zone with a 25 m.p.h. speed limit, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
