<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
AROUND THE NATION; 
</P>
<P>
MIAMI SHOWBOATS PUT INTO DRY DOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coach Dennis Erickson, who last week told his Miami Hurricanes to temper their 
talk, has now cracked down on showboating. At least two Hurricanes "crossed the 
line" of good taste by dancing, prancing and posing after big plays in 
Saturday's 52-24 victory at California, Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
"I wasn't very proud of it, and I know our team wasn't very proud of it," he 
said. "There's a point where it's embarrassing to the program." Erickson said 
players guilty of excessive celebrating will be benched for the rest of the 
game and possibly longer. 
</P>
<P>
All-American cornerback Todd Lyght suffered reinjury of a pulled hamstring and 
might be sidelined for Saturday's game with No. 24 Michigan State, Notre Dame 
Coach Lou Holtz said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
