</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAIRPLEX; 
</P>
<P>
YES I'M BLUE WINS AGAIN IN AN UPSET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BURGART, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scoring his second stakes upset of the summer, Yes I'm Blue came from last to 
defeat Southern California speedster Valiant Pete in the $52,550 Aprisa 
Handicap Tuesday afternoon at Fairplex Park. In June, Yes I'm Blue humbled 
Northern California sprint star Valley Land in a stakes race at Pleasanton. 
</P>
<P>
Dropping back to last in the field of six sprinters, Yes I'm Blue moved to the 
outside approaching the far turn and blew past 4-5 favorite Valiant Pete in the 
final sixteenth, posting a 1 1/2-length victory. Movinglikeawinner was another 
three-quarters back in the six-furlong feature. 
</P>
<P>
Yes I'm Blue surged down the stretch, running the six furlongs in 1:09 2/5, a 
fifth of a second off Drouilly's Boy's track record. Sent off at 5-1, Yes I'm 
Blue paid $12.60 and increased his lifetime earnings to $217,010. 
</P>
<P>
Fairplex Notes 
</P>
<P>
For the second straight day, nobody tabbed six winners in the Pick Six. Today's 
carry-over is $41,887. . . . Beyond Perfection, regarded as one of the 
country's top 2-year-old thoroughbred fillies, is the heavy favorite in today's 
$150,000 Barretts Debutante at 6 1/2 furlongs. In her last race, Beyond 
Perfection won the Grade II Del Mar Debutante Stakes by nine lengths, covering 
a mile in 1:34 4/5. 
</P>
<P>
Ray Sibille was the riding star Tuesday, recording a triple aboard longshots 
Lou's Good Morning ($17.20), Viznaga ($94.40) and Vice Dancer ($25.40). David 
Flores and Julio Garcia each had a victory and remained deadlocked for the 
jockey lead with nine apiece. . . . Story Book Ending, a 3-year-old maiden 
filly, collapsed and died of a ruptured heart shortly after finishing sixth in 
the seventh race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
