<TEXT>
<P>
Dr. Herbert Stark, a hand surgeon who operated on or treated athletes such as 
Jerry West, Wilt Chamberlain, Sandy Koufax and Bill Shoemaker, died at his home 
in South Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
He was 68. 
</P>
<P>
Stark, who had suffered from liver cancer, retired from active practice earlier 
this year. 
</P>
<P>
Services will be held Saturday at 9:30 a.m. at Calvary Presbyterian Church in 
South Pasadena. 
</P>
