<P>
PEOPLE: MAXWELL TO RETIRE AS CHAIRMAN OF FANNIE MAE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David O. Maxwell will retire as chairman of the Federal National Mortgage Assn. 
effective Jan. 31. 
</P>
<P>
He will be replaced by Vice Chairman James A. Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
Roger E. Birk will continue as president of Fannie Mae, a congressionally 
chartered, shareholder-owned company and the nation's largest investor in home 
mortgages. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson joined Fannie Mae in January from Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc., where he 
was a managing director. He also served as president of Public Strategies, a 
Washington consulting firm, and worked as an executive assistant to former Vice 
President Walter Mondale. 
</P>
