<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons and Tom McQueeney 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHRINKING: The number of people living outside cities in Orange County, above, 
could be halved within a year or so. . . . Incorporation efforts are well under 
way in El Toro and Laguna Hills, and the first steps are being taken in North 
Tustin. . . . Together the three areas have a population of 110,000. If they 
incorporate, about 95% of all county residents would be living within 32 
cities. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Growth Of The Cities 
</P>
<P>
Orange County's population in city versus unincorporated county territory 
</P>
