<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECTS CAUGHT IN ARMED ROBBERY OF BEAUTY SUPPLY STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT LAIT, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man and a woman were arrested Tuesday on suspicion of taking $100 at gunpoint 
from a beauty supply store, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The robbery occurred shortly after 1 p.m. when a man walked into Regal Beauty 
Supply and demanded money after showing the store's lone employee a handgun, 
Police Sgt. Bob Gustafson said. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman then fled the store with the money and ran to a blue pickup parked 
outside the store in the 800 block of North Tustin Street, Gustafson said. 
</P>
<P>
The store employee ran out of the shop and yelled to two passers-by that she 
had been robbed, Gustafson said. 
</P>
<P>
The passers-by followed the gunman, who turned to them before getting into the 
truck, pointed the gun at them and warned them not to get involved, Gustafson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman got into the passenger side of the truck, and the woman drove off. 
</P>
<P>
The passers-by followed the suspects in their car but stopped when the gunman 
got out of the truck and "again pointed a gun at them and told them to quit 
following," Gustafson said. Moments later, a police officer spotted the 
suspects' truck, pulled it over and arrested them. The money was recovered, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Booked on suspicion of robbery were Danny Lee White, 40, of no known address, 
and Jeanette Carpenter Jorgensen, 38, of Chino. 
</P>
</TEXT>
