<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIES AFTER FALL FROM OVERPASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man died Tuesday after falling onto the Riverside Freeway from 
an overpass, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police have not determined whether the man accidentally fell or jumped. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred on the Riverdale Avenue overpass about 5 p.m., Police Lt. 
Ray Welch said. The victim landed on the eastbound shoulder of the freeway and 
was not struck by a vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he was pronounced 
dead, Welch said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
