<TEXT>
<P>
The Buffalo Bills today waived fullback Larry Kinnebrew, their second-leading 
rusher last year, and re-signed punter Rick Tuten to shore up their kicking 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Tuten was released at the end of training camp when the team decided to go with 
rookie punter John Nies. 
</P>
<P>
But after Nies averaged 34.8 yards on five punts in Sunday's 30-7 loss at 
Miami, Coach Marv Levy announced he was giving serious thought to making a 
change at the position. 
</P>
<P>
Levy was not immediately available to explain why the team decided to make room 
for Tuten by releasing Kinnebrew, rather than Nies. 
</P>
<P>
